    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Hibbertia bracteata are exhibited through its antioxidant activity, which is attributed to the presence of flavonoids and phenolic acids, allowing it to protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. Additionally, this plant displays antimicrobial properties, which are largely due to the action of its saponins and volatile oils, effectively inhibiting the growth of various microorganisms and preventing infections. Hibbertia bracteata also possesses anti-inflammatory properties, resulting from the modulation of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines by its bioactive compounds, such as flavonoids and phenolic acids, leading to a reduction in inflammation and tissue damage. The antifungal properties of this plant are attributed to the presence of terpenoids and other secondary metabolites, which interfere with fungal cell membrane integrity and inhibit fungal growth. Furthermore, Hibbertia bracteata exhibits analgesic properties, which are likely due to the action of its bioactive compounds, such as flavonoids and terpenoids, on the nervous system, providing pain relief and discomfort reduction.",
